## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="2e2fd-106">È necessario chiamare il <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry.CommitChanges%2A> metodo sulla nuova voce per rendere permanente la creazione.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2e2fd-106">You must call the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry.CommitChanges%2A> method on the new entry to make the creation permanent.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2e2fd-107">Quando si chiama questo metodo, è quindi possibile impostare valori di proprietà obbligatori sulla nuova voce.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2e2fd-107">When you call this method, you can then set mandatory property values on the new entry.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2e2fd-108">I provider hanno requisiti diversi per le proprietà che è necessario impostare prima di chiamare il <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry.CommitChanges%2A> metodo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2e2fd-108">The providers each have different requirements for properties that need to be set before a call to the <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry.CommitChanges%2A> method is made.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2e2fd-109">Se questi requisiti non vengono soddisfatti, il provider può generare un'eccezione.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2e2fd-109">If those requirements are not met, the provider might throw an exception.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="2e2fd-110">Rivolgersi al provider per determinare quali proprietà devono essere impostate prima di eseguire il commit delle modifiche.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2e2fd-110">Check with your provider to determine which properties must be set before committing changes.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="2e2fd-111">L'esempio di Visual Basic .NET seguente crea un nuovo <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry> dell'oggetto con un percorso specificato, quindi crea una nuova voce nel contenitore e lo salva.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2e2fd-111">The following Visual Basic .NET example creates a new <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry> object with a specified path, then creates a new entry in the container and saves it.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Dim strPath As String = "IIS://localhost/W3SVC/1/Root"  
' Create a new 'DirectoryEntry' object with the given path.  
Dim myDE As New DirectoryEntry(strPath)  
Dim myEntries As DirectoryEntries = myDE.Children  
' Create a new entry 'Sample' in the container.  
Dim myDirectoryEntry As DirectoryEntry = myEntries.Add("CN=Sample", myDE.SchemaClassName)  
' Save changes of entry in the 'Active Directory Domain Services'.  
myDirectoryEntry.CommitChanges()  
Console.WriteLine(myDirectoryEntry.Name + " entry is created in container.")  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="2e2fd-112">L'esempio c# seguente crea un nuovo <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry> dell'oggetto con un percorso specificato, quindi crea una nuova voce nel contenitore e lo salva.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="2e2fd-112">The following C# example creates a new <xref:System.DirectoryServices.DirectoryEntry> object with a specified path, then creates a new entry in the container and saves it.</span></span>  
  
